TASK 1 – App Exposure + Scaling

You have a deployment running a web app but it's not accessible.

Requirements
  Create a Deployment web-deploy
  Image: nginx:1.25
  Replicas: 2
  Label: app=web
  Expose it using a Service web-svc
  Type: NodePort
  Port: 80
  NodePort: 30008
  Scale deployment to 5 replicas
  Verify rollout status

Ans: 
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: web-deploy
  labels:
    app: web
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: web
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: web
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.25
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
		
>> kubectl expose deployment web-deploy --type=NodePort --labels=app=web --port=80 --target-port=80 --node-port=30008 --name=web-svc
>> kubectl scale deployment web-deploy --replicas=5
>> kubectl rollout status deployment web-deploy


TASK 2 – ConfigMap + Pod Integration

Application needs environment configuration.

Requirements
  Create ConfigMap app-config
  ENV=prod
  LOG_LEVEL=debug
  Create Pod config-pod
  Image: nginx
  Inject all ConfigMap values as environment variables
  Verify inside pod (command)

Ans: 
kubectl create configmap app-config --from-literal=ENV=prod --from-literal=LOG_LEVEL=debug

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: config-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
	envFrom: 
	- configMapRef: 
	   name: app-config

>> kubectl exec -it pod/config-pod -- env | grep LOG_LEVEL
>> kubectl exec -it pod/config-pod -- env | grep ENV

TASK 3 – PVC + Pod + Data Persistence

App needs persistent storage.

Requirements
  Create PVC data-pvc
  Size: 1Gi
  AccessMode: ReadWriteOnce
  Create Pod data-pod
  Image: busybox
  Command: sleep 3600
  Mount PVC at /data
  Exec into pod and create a file /data/test.txt
  Delete pod and recreate it
  Verify data still exists
  
Ans:
apiVersion: v1 
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata: 
   name: data-pvc
spec: 
   accessModes: 
   - ReadWriteOnce 
   resources:
      requests: 
	    storage: 1Gi 
---
apiVersion: v1 
kind: Pod 
metadata: 
   name: data-pod
spec: 
   containers: 
   - name: busybox
     image: busybox
     command: ["sleep","3600"]
     volumeMounts: 
     - name: persistent_vol
	   mountPath: /data 
   volumes: 
   - name: persistent_vol
	 persistentVolumeClaim:
	  claimName: data-pvc 

>> kubectl apply -f data-pod.yaml
>> kubectl exec -it data-pod -- touch /data/test.txt
>> kubectl delete pod data-pod 
>> kubectl apply -f data-pod.yaml 
>> kubectl exec -it data-pod -- ls /data/test.txt

TASK 4 – Ingress Routing

Two services need routing via Ingress.

Requirements
  Create 2 Deployments:
  app1 → image nginx
  app2 → image httpd
  Expose both as ClusterIP:
  svc1, svc2
  Create Ingress app-ing
  /app1 → svc1
  /app2 → svc2
  
Ans: 
>> kubectl create deployment app1 --replicas=3 --image=nginx 
>> kubectl create deployment app2 --replicas=3 --image=httpd 

>> kubectl expose deployment/app1 --port=80 --target-port=80 --name=svc1 
>> kubectl expose deployment/app2 --port=80 --target-port=80 --name=svc2	

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: app-ing
spec:
  rules:
  - http:
      paths:
      - path: /app1
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: svc1 
            port:
              number: 80
	  - path: /app2
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: svc2 
            port:
              number: 80

   
